{"title_page": "The Circle (French TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|French reality television show}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name             = The Circle France\n| image                 = The Circle France.png\n| caption               = The official title screen for ''The Circle France''.\n| genre                 = [[Reality television|Reality competition]]\n| creative_director     = \n| presenter             = ''None''\n| narrated              = \n| country               = [[France]]\n| theme_music_composer  = \n| opentheme             = \n| language              = French\n| num_series            = 1\n| num_episodes          = 12\n| executive_producer    = \n| camera                = \n| runtime               = 37\u201351 minutes\n| channel               = [[Netflix]]\n| company               = [[Studio Lambert]]\n| distributor           = \n| picture_format        = \n| audio_format          = \n| released              = {{Start date|2020|4|9|df=yes}}\n| related               = {{Plainlist|\n* ''[[The Circle (British TV series)|The Circle UK]]''\n* ''[[The Circle (American TV series)|The Circle US]]''\n* ''[[The Circle (Brazilian TV series)|The Circle Brazil]]''\n}}\n| website               = https://www.thecirclecasting.com/the-circle-france\n}}\n\n'''''The Circle France''''' (also known as '''''The Circle Game''''' in [[France]])<ref name=\"trailer\">{{cite web |title=Season 1 Trailer: The Circle France |url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81189754?trackId=13752289&tctx=0%2C0%2C30a8b6b7-19b1-47c5-82ed-01092634917d-7331629%2C%2C&t=0 |website=netflix.com |publisher=Netflix |accessdate=26 March 2020 |language=French |date=26 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> is a French [[Reality television|reality competition]] show, produced by [[Studio Lambert]] and Motion Content Group which first aired on [[Netflix]] in 9 April 2020 that is based on a [[The Circle (British TV series)|British TV series of the same name]].<ref name=\"deadline\">{{cite web |last1=White |first1=Peter |title='The Circle': Netflix Lines Up French & Brazilian Remakes As Studio Lambert Uses UK Hub For Reality Format |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/the-circle-netflix-france-brazil-1202519369/ |website=deadline.com |publisher=Deadline |accessdate=16 October 2019 |date=18 December 2018}}</ref> Along with ''The Circle France'', Netflix also released separate versions of ''[[The Circle (franchise)|The Circle]]'' in the [[United States]] and [[Brazil]].<ref name=\"hollywood_reporter\">{{cite web |last1=Elise Sandberg |first1=Bryn |title=Netflix to Adapt U.K. Reality Series 'The Circle' |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/netflix-adapt-uk-reality-series-circle-1150330 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=6 June 2019}}</ref> The show bills itself as a game based around social media, with the concept that \"anyone can be anyone in ''The Circle''\". It has been compared to ''[[Big Brother (franchise)|Big Brother]]'' and ''[[Catfish: The TV Show|Catfish]]'' in format,<ref name=\"deadline\"/> as well as ''[[Black Mirror]]'' episode \"[[Nosedive (Black Mirror)|Nosedive]]\" with the concept of ratings.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Abdulbaki |first1=Mae |title=Netflix's New Reality Competition The Circle Is Already Super Popular In The U.K. |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/television/2480934/netflixs-new-reality-competition-the-circle-is-already-super-popular-in-the-uk |website=Cinema Blend |accessdate=29 September 2019 |date=26 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April 2020, the season was won by Romain Ben, who had played the game as himself, and won the [[Euro|\u20ac]]100,000 ({{USD|110000}}) prize that came along with it. \u00c9l\u00e9a was the runner-up.\n\n== Format ==\nThe contestants, or \"players\", move into the same apartment building. However, the contestants do not meet face-to-face during the course of the competition, as they each live in their own individual apartment. They communicate solely using their profiles on a specially-designed [[social media]] app that gives them the ability to portray themselves in any way they choose. Players can thus opt to present themselves as a completely different personality to the other players, a tactic otherwise known as [[catfishing]]; for example, one male player in the first season presented himself as a female identity, while another female contestant used photos of a woman she felt was more attractive.<ref name=\"polygon\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/entertainment/2020/1/10/21058661/the-circle-review-netflix-new-reality-show-catfishing|title=Netflix's The Circle is the sweetest reality show about catfishing|first=Ben|last=Kuchera|language=en-us|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=10 January 2020|work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref>\n\nThroughout the series, the contestants \"rate\" one another from first to last place. At the end of the ratings, their average ratings are revealed to one another from lowest to highest. Normally, the two highest-rated players become \"influencers\", while the remaining players will be at risk of being \"blocked\" by the influencers. However, occasionally there may be a twist to the blocking process \u2013 varying from the lowest rating players being instantly blocked, the identity of the influencers being a secret, or multiple players being blocked at one time. Blocked players are eliminated from the game, but are given the opportunity to meet one player still in the game in-person. Then, the day after a blocking, a video message is shown to the remaining players to reveal if they were real or fake.<ref name=\"polygon\"/>\n\nDuring the finale, the contestants rate each other one final time, where the highest rated player wins the game and [[Euro|\u20ac]]100,000 ({{USD|110000}}).<ref name=\"trailer\"/>\n\n== Players ==\nThe players were selected from the \"20\u201325 individuals\" being cleared to appear on the show, with the remaining people never leaving standby status and not appearing on the show.<ref name=\"variety interview 1\">{{cite web |last1=Turchiano |first1=Danielle |title='The Circle' Boss on Connecting 'People Who Otherwise Might Not Have Come into Contact with Each Other' \u2014 And Catfishing |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/features/the-circle-netflix-american-tim-harcourt-catfish-interview-1203449625/ |website=variety.com |publisher=Variety |accessdate=2 January 2020 |date=1 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The first nine players were revealed on ''The Circle France''{{'}}s [[Instagram]] profile.<ref>{{cite web |author1=@circlegame |title=Qui d'autre ne peut pas attendre! \ud83d\ude4c regardez les joueurs entrer dans The Circle Tomorrow sur @NetflixFR |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-tq9EsAU9X/ |website=instagram.com |publisher=Instagram |accessdate=8 April 2020 |date=8 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The players' profiles were revealed as they introduced themselves on-screen during an episode.<ref name=\"insider\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.craveyoutv.com/exclusive-interview-whats-next-for-best-friend-bill-from-the-circle/|title=Exclusive Interview: What's Next for Best Friend Bill from 'The Circle'|last=Buczak|first=Lizzy|date=2020-02-25|website=CraveyouTV TV Show Recaps, TV Reviews, Spoilers, Interviews|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Name\n! Age\n! Hometown\n! Playing as\n! Entered\n! Exit\n! Status\n|-\n| Lou Baudry\n| 22\n| [[Marseille]]\n| Herself\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 2\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Josette \"Jo\" Gu\u00e9rin\n| 78\n| ''Unknown''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Two friends playing jointly as 25-year-old \"Nicolas\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Episode 1\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Episode 4\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Monique\n| 75\n| ''Unknown''\n|-\n| C\u00e9dric Doumbe\n| 27\n| [[Bordeaux]]\n| Himself\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 6\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Gary Jarny\n| 30\n| [[Les Sables-d'Olonne]]\n| Himself\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 8\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Ines Camilia Tazi\n| 23\n| [[London]]\n| Herself, but single\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 9\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Paolo\n| 21\n| [[Chatou]]\n| Himself\n| Episode 6\n| Episode 10\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Catala \"Virginie\" Constance\n| 28\n| [[Avignon]]\n| Herself, but a single 30-year-old [[gynecologist]]\n| Episode 8\n| Episode 11\n| style=\"background:#f4c7b8;\" | Blocked\n|-\n| Maxime Merkouchenko\n| 24\n| [[French Riviera]] / [[Monaco]]\n| \"Valeria\", his 25-year-old girlfriend\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 12\n| style=\"background:#F5FF80;\" | {{nowrap|Fifth place}}\n|-\n| Edmundo\n| 24\n| [[London]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| \"Nelia\", a 25-year-old fashion [[Blog|blogger]] from [[Toulouse]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Episode 4\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Episode 12\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#F5FF80;\" | {{nowrap|Fourth place}}\n|-\n| Jo\u00e3o\n| 24\n| [[London]]\n|-\n| Rudy Doukhan\n| 37\n| [[Marseille]]\n| \"Gabriel\", a single 32-year-old father\n| Episode 3\n| Episode 12\n| style=\"background:tan;\" | {{nowrap|Third place}}\n|-\n| \u00c9l\u00e9a\n| 27\n| [[Nice]]\n| Herself\n| Episode 1\n| Episode 12\n| style=\"background:silver;\" | {{nowrap|Runner-up}}\n|-style=\"background:lavender;\"\n| '''Romain Ben'''\n| '''28'''\n| '''[[Paris]]'''\n| '''Himself'''\n| '''Episode 1'''\n| '''Episode 12'''\n| style=\"background:gold;\" | '''Winner'''\n|}\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Episode table\n| total_width=100\n| background=#EE6161\n| overall=4\n| season=4\n| title=30\n| airdate=20\n| episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = Hello Circle\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|9|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = The first nine players entered The Circle and created their profiles, including their name, age, hometown, and a short [[Biography|bio]]. Immediately after, the players were shown everyo