erican photographer (d. 1979)\n*  1891   &ndash; [[Vittorio Jano]], Italian engineer (d. 1965)\n*  1891   &ndash; [[Harold Jeffreys]], English mathematician, geophysicist, and astronomer (d. 1989)\n*  1891   &ndash; [[Sacco and Vanzetti|Nicola Sacco]], Italian-American anarchist (d. 1927)\n*[[1892]] &ndash; [[Vernon Johns]], African-American minister and activist (d. 1965)\n*[[1899]] &ndash; [[Vladimir Nabokov]], Russian-born novelist and critic (d. 1977)\n*[[1900]] &ndash; [[Nellie Beer]], British politician, Lord Mayor of [[Manchester]] from 1966\u201367 (d. 1988) <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abitofhistory.net/html/rhw/b_body.htm|title=Women of History - B|website=abitofhistory.net|access-date=2017-10-19}}</ref>\n*[[1904]] &ndash; [[J. Robert Oppenheimer]], American physicist and academic (d. 1967)\n*[[1905]] &ndash; [[Robert Choquette]], American-Canadian author, poet, and diplomat (d. 1991)\n*[[190]]  &ndash; [[Eric Fenby]], English composer and educator (d. 1997)\n* 1906    &ndash; [[Prince Gustaf Adolf, Duke of V\u00e4sterbotten]] (d. 1947)\n*[[1908]] &ndash; [[Ivan Yefremov]], Russian paleontologist and author (d. 1972)\n*[[1909]] &ndash; [[Rita Levi-Montalcini]], [[Sephardic]] Jewish-Italian neurologist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 2012)\n* 1909 &ndash; [[Indro Montanelli]], Italian journalist and historian (d. 2001)\n* 1909 &ndash; [[Spyros Markezinis]], Greek politician, [[Prime Minister of Greece]] (d. 2000)\n*[[1910]] &ndash; [[Norman Steenrod]], American mathematician and academic (d. 1971)\n*[[1912]] &ndash; [[Kathleen Ferrier]], English operatic singer (d. 1953)\n* 1912 &ndash; [[Kaneto Shindo]], Japanese director, producer, and screenwriter (d. 2012)\n*[[1914]] &ndash; [[Baldev Raj Chopra]], Indian director and producer (d. 2008)\n* 1914 &ndash; [[Jan de Hartog]], Dutch-American author and playwright (d. 2002)\n* 1914 &ndash; [[Jos\u00e9 Qui\u00f1ones Gonzales]], Peruvian soldier and pilot (d. 1941)\n