sodeNumber   = \n| EpisodeNumber2  = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB3C8\n}}\n}}\n\n==Release==\nOn January 30, 2019, it was announced during the [[Television Critics Association]]'s annual winter press tour that the series would premiere on April 1, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|last=Petski|first=Denise|title=\u2018The Twilight Zone\u2019 Gets April Premiere Date On CBS All Access \u2013 TCA|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/the-twilight-zone-april-premiere-date-cbs-all-access-1202545867/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=January 30, 2019|date=January 30, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190131010717/https://deadline.com/2019/01/the-twilight-zone-april-premiere-date-cbs-all-access-1202545867/|archive-date=January 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> A black-and-white version of the first season was released on May 30, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/05/11/cbs-all-access-twilight-zone-black-and-white/ |title=CBS All Access will stream 'Twilight Zone' in black and white |website=Engadget |first=Jon |last=Fingas |date=May 11, 2019 |accessdate=May 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nOn February 3, 2019, a teaser trailer for the series aired during the telecast of [[Super Bowl LIII]]. The commercial played as though it was interrupting CBS' feed of the game and it featured host [[Jordan Peele]] standing in an empty [[Mercedes-Benz Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=\u2018The Twilight Zone\u2019: First Spot For Series Revival \"Disrupts\" Super Bowl Telecast|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/the-twilight-zone-super-bowl-spot-jordan-peele-1202548668/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=February 3, 2019|date=February 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190204012037/https://deadline.com/2019/02/the-twilight-zone-super-bowl-spot-jordan-peele-1202548668/|archive-date=February 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Another trailer was released on February 21.<ref name=\"TrailerCast\">{{cite web|last=Baysinger|first=Tim|title='Twilight Zone' Trailer: See Adam Scott, Sanaa Lathan and Tracy Morgan Enter The Fifth Dimension|url=https://www.thewrap.com/twilight-zone-trailer-see-adam-scott-sanaa-lathan-and-tracy-morgan-enter-the-fifth-dimension-video/|website=TheWrap|accessdate=February 21, 2019|date=February 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222013659/https://www.thewrap.com/twilight-zone-trailer-see-adam-scott-sanaa-lathan-and-tracy-morgan-enter-the-fifth-dimension-video/|archive-date=February 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nOn the review aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the first season holds an approval rating of 71% based on 86 reviews, with an average rating of 7.39/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''The Twilight Zone'' explores the strangeness of the modern world through Rod Serling's winning formula, creating a thought-provoking \u2013 if not always spine-tingling \u2013 showcase for Jordan Peele and his exceptional crop of collaborators.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/the_twilight_zone_2019/s01|title=The Twilight Zone: Season 1 (2019)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] assigned the first season a weighted average score of 60 out of 100 based on 37 critics, indicating \"generally positive reviews.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/the-twilight-zone-2019/season-1|title=The Twilight Zone (2019) : Season 1|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[BBC]] gave it a positive review and said: \"It's possible that ... Rod Serling and Jordan Peele switched places. As co-creator and on-screen host of the new version, he [Peele] updates the series while capturing the original's essence.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/culture/story/20190401-the-twilight-zone-eerie-witty-stylishly-told-stories|title=The Twilight Zone: Eerie, witty, stylishly told stories|website=BBC|first=Caryn|last=James|date=April 2, 2019|accessdate=April 25, 2019}}</ref> ''[[The Week]]'' was more mixed in its review, calling the first episodes \"unforgivably long\", but also saying that the series stays \"true to the ethos of ''The Twilight Zone''\" and that \"the episodes are free-standing and timeless\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theweek.com/articles/832528/jordan-peeles-twilight-zone-unforgivably-long|title=Jordan Peele's Twilight Zone is Unforgivably Long|website=The Week|first=Java|last=Lange|date=April 2, 2019|accessdate=April 25, 2019}}</ref> ''[[The Verge]]'' also gave it a mixed review, praising Jordan Peele as the narrator, but saying the series should try to step away from the original.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/4/1/18287537/jordan-peele-twilight-zone-reboot-review-cbs-adam-scott-steven-yuen-kumail-nanjiani-tracy-morgan|title=Jordan Peele's Twilight Zone reboot leans too heavily on the original|website=The Verge|first=Samantha|last=Nelson|date=April 1, 2019|accessdate=April 25, 2019}}</ref> ''[[The Atlantic]]'' was more critical, comparing it to the original series, stating, \"[w]ith the exception of one superior episode, 'Replay', it's hard to conceive that an artist as prodigiously talented and thoughtful as Peele is creatively involved at all.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Gilbert|first1=Sophie|title=What the Twilight Zone Reboot Is Missing|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2019/04/jordan-peeles-twilight-zone-reboot-missing-something/586396/|website=The Atlantic|accessdate=April 19, 2019|date=April 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\nFor the [[71st Primetime Emmy Awards]], [[Kumail Nanjiani]] received a nomination for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Guest Actor in a Drama Series]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/16/arts/television/emmy-nominations-list.html |title=Here's a Full List of the 2019 Emmy Nominations |work=The New York Times |first=Sara |last=Aridi |date=July 16, 2019 |accessdate=July 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official|https://www.cbs.com/shows/the-twilight-zone/}}\n* {{IMDb title|2583620}}\n\n{{Twilight Zone}}\n{{Jordan Peele}}\n{{Simon Kinberg}}\n{{CBS All Access}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Twilight Zone, The}}\n\n[[Category:2010s American anthology television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:2019 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:CBS All Access original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Fantasy web series]]\n[[Category:Horror anthology web series]]\n[[Category:Science fiction anthology web series]]\n[[Category:Television series by CBS Television Studios]]\n[[Category:Television series created by Jordan Peele]]\n[[Category:Television series created by Simon Kinberg]]\n[[Category:Television series produced in Vancouver]]\n[[Category:Television series reboots]]\n[[Category:The Twilight Zone]]\n", "name_user": "WhisperToMe", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSeason 1 (2019)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Twilight_Zone_(2019_TV_series)"}
